00:28:20.200 --> 00:28:22.995
and so the rats lived
up to those expectations.

510
00:28:24.913 --> 00:28:26.113
Why are we talking about this?

511
00:28:27.958 --> 00:28:29.501
Because I am the rat.

512
00:28:31.003 --> 00:28:32.880
And if you think I'm gonna fail. I'm…

513
00:28:33.922 --> 00:28:35.799
Probably will.

514
00:28:42.014 --> 00:28:43.182
Anyway.

515
00:28:47.227 --> 00:28:50.981
Maybe it's time you let me find
my way out of the maze by myself.

516
00:28:55.611 --> 00:28:57.422
Tori. hey.

517
00:28:57.446 --> 00:28:59.072
I can't with mom. I'm moving in.

518
00:29:04.328 --> 00:29:05.746
You saw her too. right?

519
00:29:13.837 --> 00:29:15.773
<i>First my back went out.</i>

520
00:29:15.797 --> 00:29:17.424
<i>Then I got caught red-handed.</i>

521
00:29:17.925 --> 00:29:20.361
<i>Now I had pawned
something for 100.000 bucks</i>

522
00:29:20.385 --> 00:29:23.055
<i>that I would have to buy
back for twice that. at minimum.</i>

523
00:29:23.639 --> 00:29:26.367
<i>It was all putting a
serious dent in my pride.</i>

524
00:29:26.391 --> 00:29:27.893
<i>Not to mention my cash flow.</i>

525
00:29:28.894 --> 00:29:30.121
<i>And the irony was.</i>

526
00:29:30.145 --> 00:29:33.041
<i>I would have to hit multiple
houses at the exact moment</i>

527
00:29:33.065 --> 00:29:35.692
<i>I was starting to wonder if
I was even any good at it.</i>

528
00:29:36.610 --> 00:29:37.611
Right this way. sir.

529
00:29:42.449 --> 00:29:43.450
What the fuck?

530
00:29:46.328 --> 00:29:47.329
Ashe?

531
00:29:48.497 --> 00:29:49.498
Surprised?

532
00:29:51.041 --> 00:29:52.292
Surprised is a word.

533
00:29:53.377 --> 00:29:54.378
I'm the buyer.

534
00:29:56.964 --> 00:29:58.024
What?

535
00:29:58.048 --> 00:29:59.049
Bon appétit.

536
00:30:00.634 --> 00:30:02.070
You have to try this crudo. man.

537
00:30:02.094 --> 00:30:03.095
It's fucking insane.

538
00:30:04.346 --> 00:30:05.949
You bought your own book back?

539
00:30:05.973 --> 00:30:07.975
Yeah. I told you. It means a lot to me.

540
00:30:08.851 --> 00:30:10.435
How did you track it down?

541
00:30:11.395 --> 00:30:14.415
Well. the hot books
market's not really a large one.

542
00:30:14.439 --> 00:30:18.253
So. this whole idea of me chasing around
trying to find it. that was just for fun?

543
00:30:18.277 --> 00:30:19.629
Exactly. Team building.

544
00:30:19.653 --> 00:30:22.239
Okay. Well. no harm. no foul.

545
00:30:24.491 --> 00:30:26.511
Wait. I'm still out 200 grand.

546
00:30:26.535 --> 00:30:28.805
Yeah. Here's 150.

547
00:30:28.829 --> 00:30:30.390
Give me another week.
I'll get you the rest.

548
00:30:30.414 --> 00:30:32.499
How you gonna do that? You
gonna Rob somebody else?

549
00:30:34.751 --> 00:30:36.020
Come on.

550
00:30:36.044 --> 00:30:37.254
