office of foreign assets control.

566
00:31:15.876 --> 00:31:17.002
Ofac. yes.

567
00:31:21.006 --> 00:31:23.193
How the fuck did you
get on the ofac list?

568
00:31:23.217 --> 00:31:26.154
I ship cargo all over the world.

569
00:31:26.178 --> 00:31:27.655
And let's just say the us government

570
00:31:27.679 --> 00:31:29.699
is not on speaking terms
with some of my clients.

571
00:31:29.723 --> 00:31:32.809
And the new administration
has a big. fat hard-on for me.

572
00:31:33.519 --> 00:31:36.939
My assets. such as they
are. are vulnerable to seizure.

573
00:31:37.564 --> 00:31:39.501
So I have to diversify quickly.

574
00:31:39.525 --> 00:31:41.002
You can't ask me to do that.

575
00:31:41.026 --> 00:31:43.338
- I'm not asking.
- It's against the law.

576
00:31:43.362 --> 00:31:44.756
You robbed my house.

577
00:31:44.780 --> 00:31:46.090
This is different.

578
00:31:46.114 --> 00:31:47.884
- Yeah? I don't think it is.
- Well. listen.

579
00:31:47.908 --> 00:31:50.661
Even if I could get you into
excelsior. which I cannot.

580
00:31:51.161 --> 00:31:54.081
there is no way that your
money clears compliance.

581
00:31:54.790 --> 00:31:57.070
- You're saying you can't do it?
- I'm saying no one can.

582
00:31:58.293 --> 00:32:00.254
You don't become what you want.

583
00:32:00.879 --> 00:32:02.297
You become what you believe.

584
00:32:03.924 --> 00:32:05.068
Oprah said that.

585
00:32:05.092 --> 00:32:07.028
Good. Get her to manage your portfolio.

586
00:32:07.052 --> 00:32:08.154
Come on. Coop.

587
00:32:08.178 --> 00:32:09.823
There's 17.000 people on that list.

588
00:32:09.847 --> 00:32:12.492
You seriously expect me to
believe there's not one sdn investing

589
00:32:12.516 --> 00:32:13.559
in Bailey Russell funds?

590
00:32:17.312 --> 00:32:18.873
Look. man. It's a zero-sum game.

591
00:32:18.897 --> 00:32:21.775
You can help me out.
or you can get arrested…

592
00:32:22.484 --> 00:32:23.545
Again.

593
00:32:23.569 --> 00:32:25.547
So now it's just straight blackmail?

594
00:32:25.571 --> 00:32:26.572
Look…

595
00:32:27.281 --> 00:32:28.532
We're driven men. you and I.

596
00:32:29.616 --> 00:32:31.219
We've worked hard for what is ours.

597
00:32:31.243 --> 00:32:33.245
and we'll do what we
have to do to keep it.

598
00:32:34.371 --> 00:32:35.622
So I know you get it.

599
00:32:37.416 --> 00:32:39.668
I'll give you 48 hours
to come up with a plan.

600
00:32:41.003 --> 00:32:42.689
Do you wanna split a chocolate cake?

601
00:32:42.713 --> 00:32:43.773
How are you with gluten?

602
00:32:43.797 --> 00:32:45.191
Can we get two forks. please?

603
00:32:45.215 --> 00:32:48.027
<i>There are moments in your
life that you regret in hindsight.</i>

604
00:32:48.051 --> 00:32:50.738
<i>And then there are the
moments you're already regretting</i>

605
00:32:50.762 --> 00:32:52.556
<i>even while they're still happening.</i>

606
00:32:55.267 --> 00:32:57.871
<i>I knew it was a bad idea to
get involved with Owen ashe.</i>

607
00:32:57.895 --> 00:33:00.022
<i>but I couldn't see a way out of it.</i>

608
00:33:00.606 --> 00:33:03.585
<i>And if nothing else. I had to
marvel at my unrivaled ability</i>

609
00:33:03.609 --> 00:33:07.112
<i>to take a bad situation
and make it so much worse.</i>

610
00:33:12.117 --> 00:33:13.118
Beep.

611
00:33:14.244 --> 00:33:15.746
Lehayim.

612
00:33:17.539 --> 00:33:18.749
How's your new roommate?

613
00:33:20.417 --> 00:33:23.086
I'll let you know once
she starts talking to me.

614
00:33:23.962 --> 00:33:25.047
How are you?

615
00:33:26.340 --> 00:33:27.591
You know. I've been better.

616
00:33:28.509 --> 00:33:30.093
You know why she came to you. right?

617
00:33:31.053 --> 00:33:32.221
Because I'm her father.

618
00:33:32.930 --> 00:33:34.473
'Cause you're the vacation parent.

619
00:33:35.057 --> 00:33:36.183
The fun one.

620
00:33:36.892 --> 00:33:38.703
Okay. are you mad
because she's pissed at you.

621
00:33:38.727 --> 00:33:40.229
or because she came to me?

622
00:33:41.063 --> 00:33:42.499
- Seriously.
- You were always at work.

623
00:33:42.523 --> 00:33:44.626
I was the one who had to hold the line.

624
00:33:44.650 --> 00:33:47.295
You'd maybe emerge for a
couple of hours on weekends.

625
00:33:47.319 --> 00:33:48.612
but all bets were off.

626
00:33:49.238 --> 00:33:50.781
You never said no to her.

627
00:33:52.533 --> 00:33:53.927
She was always so good.

628
00:33:53.951 --> 00:33:55.637
She was good because I was on it.

629
00:33:55.661 --> 00:33:58.765
"Brush your teeth. Drink your milk.
Do your homework. Be home by 11:00.

630
00:33:58.789 --> 00:34:00.683
Get off your screens.

631
00:34:00.707 --> 00:34:02.626
You can't leave the
house wearing that outfit."

632
00:34:03.544 --> 00:34:05.480
Whenever they came to you
for permission for something.

633
00:34:05.504 --> 00:34:07.732
you'd be like. "what did mom say?"

634
00:34:07.756 --> 00:34:09.483
Yeah. 'cause I was backing you up.

635
00:34:09.507 --> 00:34:10.652
You were passing the buck.

636
00:34:10.676 --> 00:34:12.177
Please.

637
00:34:14.179 --> 00:34:18.326
I gave everything I had to those
kids. and somehow I'm the asshole.

638
00:34:18.350 --> 00:34:19.976
Well. if the shoe fits.

639
00:34:21.562 --> 00:34:22.563
Come on.

640
00:34:26.315 --> 00:34:28.294
Girls push back against their mothers.

641
00:34:28.318 --> 00:34:30.529
It's a thing. It'll pass.

642
00:34:31.947 --> 00:34:34.008
I guess you're just thrilled
you get her all to yourself.

643
00:34:34.032 --> 00:34:36.284
Well. it's not the worst.

644
00:34:37.619 --> 00:34:40.121
If I'm being honest. my
house can be a little lonely.

645
00:34:41.123 --> 00:34:44.018
I mean. I lived with
you guys for 18 years.

646
00:34:44.042 --> 00:34:47.438
It's honestly kind of nice
to have her slamming doors

647
00:34:47.462 --> 00:34:49.047
and rolling her eyes at me.

648
00:34:50.632 --> 00:34:51.675
Ain't it?

649
00:34:56.554 --> 00:34:58.140
This will run its course. Mel.

650
00:34:59.641 --> 00:35:00.976
She's gonna need her mom.

651
00:35:02.769 --> 00:35:04.271
But she's gonna be gone soon.

652
00:35:05.689 --> 00:35:06.690
Yeah.

653
00:35:07.357 --> 00:35:09.651
Even if she doesn't go to college. she's…

654
00:35:11.778 --> 00:35:13.030
Off on her way.

655
00:35:15.741 --> 00:35:17.552
God. it just doesn't seem that long ago

656
00:35:17.576 --> 00:35:19.620
we brought her home
from the hospital. does it?

657
00:35:21.038 --> 00:35:23.123
Yeah. I remember the hospital.

658
00:35:23.874 --> 00:35:26.227
You came to pick us up
and forgot where you parked.

659
00:35:26.251 --> 00:35:28.396
Well. I was a little bit stressed. It was…

660
00:35:28.420 --> 00:35:29.689
- Walking around…
- first kid.

661
00:35:29.713 --> 00:35:31.232
…the parking structure for an hour.

662
00:35:31.256 --> 00:35:32.424
Twenty minutes. tops.

663
00:35:33.050 --> 00:35:35.528
God. you thought Tori
was gonna die of exposure.

664
00:35:35.552 --> 00:35:36.637
It was cold.

665
00:35:38.180 --> 00:35:39.515
No. it wasn't.

666
00:35:41.975 --> 00:35:43.244
First kid.

667
00:35:43.268 --> 00:35:44.311
Yeah.

668
00:35:45.145 --> 00:35:46.146
For sure.

669
00:35:52.444 --> 00:35:56.174
You have these kids. this
family. and it's your whole world.

670
00:35:56.198 --> 00:35:58.367
And then you realize everybody leaves.

671
00:36:01.787 --> 00:36:04.456
First Tori's gonna go.
then hunter and then…

672
00:36:07.668 --> 00:36:08.919
Who am I gonna be?

673
00:36:10.796 --> 00:36:13.674
Some lonely old hag
living in a big empty house.

674
00:36:17.302 --> 00:36:19.572
Well. I mean. if you wanna
downsize. we can talk about it.

675
00:36:19.596 --> 00:36:21.348
No fucking way. Get outta here.

676
00:36:33.110 --> 00:36:34.736
How the hell did this happen?

677
00:36:37.531 --> 00:36:39.324
We were never supposed to get this old.

678
00:36:45.831 --> 00:36:47.124
We blinked.

679
00:36:55.924 --> 00:36:57.009
Hey…

680
00:36:58.844 --> 00:36:59.904
Not a big deal.

681
00:36:59.928 --> 00:37:05.851
but I just got a bill for $3.000 for
something called a Mona Lisa?

682
00:37:07.186 --> 00:37:10.147
That is a skin treatment. It's…

683
00:37:11.148 --> 00:37:12.316
- All right.
- For your…

684
00:37:13.358 --> 00:37:14.359
Yeah.

685
00:37:15.736 --> 00:37:16.737
Smile.

686
00:37:18.530 --> 00:37:21.593
<i>Yeah. everyone's mad on social
media complaining about ratings</i>

687
00:37:21.617 --> 00:37:23.094
<i>saying they want the '90s back.</i>

688
00:37:23.118 --> 00:37:24.929
- <i>And then those same folks complain…</i>
- whiskey.

689
00:37:24.953 --> 00:37:28.224
<i>- …as soon as they have to…</i>
- hey. - Hey.

690
00:37:28.248 --> 00:37:29.809
Hey. Look at that.

691
00:37:29.833 --> 00:37:32.604
<i>Don't tell me the patron Saint
of flopping is weighing in on this.</i>

692
00:37:32.628 --> 00:37:34.772
<i>I know you're talking to him and not me.</i>

693
00:37:34.796 --> 00:37:36.882
Yeah. Already took out my usual fee.

694
00:37:41.470 --> 00:37:43.406
Kwan park technologies.

695
00:37:43.430 --> 00:37:44.824
Your father-in-law. Very clever.

696
00:37:44.848 --> 00:37:46.058
Yeah.

697
00:37:46.850 --> 00:37:48.286
Now I get to pay taxes.

698
00:37:48.310 --> 00:37:50.312
Well. legitimate income's expensive.

699
00:37:52.064 --> 00:37:55.108
<i>I was just very fall-prone.
Vertigo and whatnot…</i>

700
00:37:56.026 --> 00:37:58.880
It would help if I had some
sense of future cash flow.

701
00:37:58.904 --> 00:38:00.006
Yeah. about that.

702
00:38:00.030 --> 00:38:04.385
Things are gonna be a
little quiet for some time.

703
00:38:04.409 --> 00:38:06.328
Quiet? I just got everything set up.

704
00:38:08.497 --> 00:38:10.350
- What did you do?
- I got caught.

705
00:38:10.374 --> 00:38:11.625
I'm sorry. what?

706
00:38:12.835 --> 00:38:13.937
Coop. am I exposed here?

707
00:38:13.961 --> 00:38:15.396
You're fine. Jesus. Barney.

708
00:38:15.420 --> 00:38:17.631
It's a legit question. Who caught you?

709
00:38:18.924 --> 00:38:20.485
Owen ashe.

710
00:38:20.509 --> 00:38:23.112
- Why the hell would you Rob ashe?
- Why the hell wouldn't I?

711
00:38:23.136 --> 00:38:25.949
He's like some kind of
arms dealer or something.

712
00:38:25.973 --> 00:38:27.975
- Is that true?
- I don't know. That's the rumor.

713
00:38:29.184 --> 00:38:32.229
Well. now he wants me to
manage an investment for him.

714
00:38:34.106 --> 00:38:36.876
So. he caught you robbing his
house and now he wants to hire you?

715
00:38:36.900 --> 00:38:38.002
What am I missing here?

716
00:38:38.026 --> 00:38:39.444
He's on the ofac list.

717
00:38:41.488 --> 00:38:43.115
- Shit.
- Yeah.

718
00:38:43.615 --> 00:38:45.242
It's a sizable investment.

719
00:38:46.743 --> 00:38:47.911
How sizable?

720
00:38:49.079 --> 00:38:50.455
Extra large.

721
00:38:54.251 --> 00:38:55.502
Controversial thought.

722
00:38:56.420 --> 00:38:59.047
Maybe this is your ticket
back to the big game.

723
00:39:00.090 --> 00:39:01.734
You are taking this surprisingly well.

724
00:39:01.758 --> 00:39:02.759
I know. right?

725
00:39:03.635 --> 00:39:05.304
Crime suits me. Who knew?

726
00:39:08.473 --> 00:39:09.558
One more.

727
00:39:16.690 --> 00:39:20.110
So. don't take this the wrong way but…

728
00:39:22.237 --> 00:39:24.656
That was better than usual.

729
00:39:27.409 --> 00:39:28.410
Good.

730
00:39:32.915 --> 00:39:34.499
What's gotten into you?

731
00:39:35.417 --> 00:39:36.418
What? Can't a…

732
00:39:37.044 --> 00:39:39.755
Can't a man put a little
energy into pleasing his wife?

733
00:39:41.215 --> 00:39:42.216
He sure can.

734
00:39:51.767 --> 00:39:52.768
Also…

735
00:39:54.895 --> 00:39:56.647
I'm not gonna work for your father.

736
00:40:04.363 --> 00:40:05.656
I'll get you a towel.

737
00:40:07.407 --> 00:40:09.093
<i>- …any more?
- Not a chance.</i>

738
00:40:09.117 --> 00:40:12.555
<i>I could see he was scared stiff
'cause he talked as much as he did.</i>

739
00:40:12.579 --> 00:40:14.057
<i>- I don't get it. Johnny.</i>
- Hey.

740
00:40:14.081 --> 00:40:15.683
<i>About these two other guys…</i>

741
00:40:15.707 --> 00:40:18.043
I'm looking up kubrick's filmography.

742
00:40:18.836 --> 00:40:20.647
Can you do it after the movie is over?

743
00:40:20.671 --> 00:40:23.024
No. I wanna be able
to contextualize as I go.

744
00:40:23.048 --> 00:40:25.133
- This is one of his first features.
- Yes. I know.

745
00:40:25.801 --> 00:40:26.927
It's impressive.

746
00:40:28.512 --> 00:40:29.680
It's fine. I guess.

747
00:40:31.640 --> 00:40:32.992
It's fine. you guess?

748
00:40:33.016 --> 00:40:35.453
- Dad.
- It's <i>the killing</i>. It's a masterpiece.

749
00:40:35.477 --> 00:40:38.272
Which I'll never get to
see if you don't press play.

750
00:40:40.399 --> 00:40:42.985
I take it you'd rather not talk about…

751
00:40:44.987 --> 00:40:47.322
- About mom-gate?
- Is that what we're calling it?

752
00:40:49.408 --> 00:40:50.468
Dad.

753
00:40:50.492 --> 00:40:52.178
It's just… I don't know.

754
00:40:52.202 --> 00:40:53.513
It's just not very evocative.

755
00:40:53.537 --> 00:40:55.372
Sorry. I haven't focus grouped it yet.

756
00:40:56.790 --> 00:40:58.417
Can we just watch the movie?

757
00:41:01.587 --> 00:41:02.880
Fine.

758
00:41:03.881 --> 00:41:06.568
<i>You mean there's gonna be
two other guys in on the deal</i>

759
00:41:06.592 --> 00:41:08.194
<i>and we ain't gonna know who they are?</i>

760
00:41:08.218 --> 00:41:10.053
<i>That's right. You know
who they are and…</i>

761
00:41:15.642 --> 00:41:16.894
This setup is insane.

762
00:41:17.603 --> 00:41:21.273
Yeah. My dad likes to flex
even when no one's looking.

763
00:41:22.691 --> 00:41:25.920
Hey. hunter. Good to see you. bud.

764
00:41:25.944 --> 00:41:26.945
Hey.

765
00:41:28.739 --> 00:41:30.675
Did you need something or…

766
00:41:30.699 --> 00:41:32.677
No. no. no. No. I just heard the music.

767
00:41:32.701 --> 00:41:34.637
It sounded nice. Wanted to
see where it was coming from.

768
00:41:34.661 --> 00:41:36.723
- You play really well.
- Thanks.

769
00:41:36.747 --> 00:41:39.791
You know. I play a pretty mean
guitar if you ever feel like jamming.

770
00:41:41.418 --> 00:41:42.419
Shit.

771
00:41:43.170 --> 00:41:44.421
Gotta tune these.

772
00:41:49.009 --> 00:41:51.845
I'm gonna bounce
and leave you guys to it.

773
00:41:52.471 --> 00:41:53.639
Good to see you. pal.

774
00:41:58.393 --> 00:41:59.728
Sorry about that.

775
00:42:00.521 --> 00:42:01.789
Was he any good?

776
00:42:01.813 --> 00:42:03.857
I don't know. I've never seen him play.

777
00:42:04.650 --> 00:42:06.961
I feel bad for all these
guitars wasting away.

778
00:42:06.985 --> 00:42:09.839
You should see his fencing gear
that he's used maybe. like. twice.

779
00:42:09.863 --> 00:42:13.283
Adhd and an unlimited
budget is a bad combination.

780
00:42:14.451 --> 00:42:16.221
Well. my dad plays golf

781
00:42:16.245 --> 00:42:18.890
and watches old movies
till he falls asleep so…

782
00:42:18.914 --> 00:42:20.123
That sounds awesome.

783
00:42:24.920 --> 00:42:28.549
You always make me look
so much... cooler. Hotter.

784
00:42:39.685 --> 00:42:41.979
You need to do something
about that girlfriend.

785
00:42:49.403 --> 00:42:50.821
Westmont pd.

786
00:42:53.115 --> 00:42:54.408
Stay here.

787
00:43:07.421 --> 00:43:09.631
Hands up! Hands up!

788
00:43:12.467 --> 00:43:13.903
- Dad!
- Andrew Cooper.

789
00:43:13.927 --> 00:43:17.264
You are under arrest for breaking
and entering and grand larceny.

790
00:43:19.600 --> 00:43:21.268
It's not yours if you can't keep it.

791
00:43:48.545 --> 00:43:49.546
Fuck.

792
00:44:00.974 --> 00:44:01.975
Hey.

793
00:44:02.643 --> 00:44:03.644
Hey.

794
00:44:04.353 --> 00:44:05.354
Warm-up shot.

795
00:44:07.689 --> 00:44:08.815
So…

796
00:44:09.650 --> 00:44:10.710
Did you come to play?

797
00:44:10.734 --> 00:44:12.444
Yeah. Something like that.

798
00:44:13.028 --> 00:44:14.947
All right. Lay it on me.

799
00:44:17.616 --> 00:44:19.010
Well…

800
00:44:19.034 --> 00:44:22.305
We're gonna need to set up
four different shell companies.

801
00:44:22.329 --> 00:44:23.765
Two overseas. two here.

802
00:44:23.789 --> 00:44:26.309
And a handful of intermediary accounts.

803
00:44:26.333 --> 00:44:28.353
Great. My guys can
take care of all of that.

804
00:44:28.377 --> 00:44:29.962
Well. I'll need to oversee it.

805
00:44:31.463 --> 00:44:33.274
The treasury department
doesn't have the resources

806
00:44:33.298 --> 00:44:34.591
to scrutinize every transaction.

807
00:44:35.175 --> 00:44:38.095
A billion dollars is not exactly
gonna fly under the radar.

808
00:44:38.762 --> 00:44:40.573
The number was 400 million.

809
00:44:40.597 --> 00:44:41.723
Where did you get a billion?

810
00:44:42.432 --> 00:44:44.226
A billion-one. actually…

811
00:44:44.893 --> 00:44:46.412
The amount of money I invest

812
00:44:46.436 --> 00:44:49.165
has to be less than 40% of
money under my management

813
00:44:49.189 --> 00:44:51.441
to avoid triggering a
kyc check at Bailey's.

814
00:44:52.192 --> 00:44:54.278
"Know your customer."

815
00:44:56.196 --> 00:44:58.949
See. this is why I need you.
'cause you know all this shit.

816
00:44:59.533 --> 00:45:02.095
So you kick back the 600
once we get into excelsior. right?

817
00:45:02.119 --> 00:45:04.097
- If we get into excelsior.
- Yeah.

818
00:45:04.121 --> 00:45:05.414
We're getting in.

819
00:45:06.748 --> 00:45:09.084
You know I take a 4% management fee.

820
00:45:10.586 --> 00:45:13.213
Your fee is me not having you arrested.

821
00:45:13.797 --> 00:45:14.798
Remember?

822
00:45:15.591 --> 00:45:17.235
Come on. Let's get loaded.

823
00:45:17.259 --> 00:45:18.677
Toast our new partnership.

824
00:45:19.428 --> 00:45:20.613
It's not a partnership.

825
00:45:20.637 --> 00:45:22.198
You're blackmailing me.

826
00:45:22.222 --> 00:45:24.224
Two things can be true at the same time.

827
00:45:38.947 --> 00:45:41.074
Hey! Hey! Hey!

828
00:45:41.742 --> 00:45:42.784
Get outta here!

829
00:45:43.535 --> 00:45:44.745
Shoo! Go on.

830
00:46:07.518 --> 00:46:08.786
- Hi.
- Hi.

831
00:46:08.810 --> 00:46:11.021
You just… you left this over at my place.

832
00:46:15.901 --> 00:46:18.963
What the… what the fuck is this?

833
00:46:18.987 --> 00:46:20.197
You're welcome.

834
00:46:47.641 --> 00:46:50.269
- Hey. what's up?
- I have our next house.

835
00:46:53.272 --> 00:46:55.834
Yeah. I… man. I don't think I can do it.

836
00:46:55.858 --> 00:46:57.794
My back's been seizing up all week.

837
00:46:57.818 --> 00:46:59.254
Come on. Coop.

838
00:46:59.278 --> 00:47:00.713
I have a good window.

839
00:47:00.737 --> 00:47:03.716
They're away for a week.
Easy in. easy out. Just like ashe.

840
00:47:03.740 --> 00:47:07.595
Well. I was feeling better then. and
now the pain's been pretty intense.

841
00:47:07.619 --> 00:47:10.557
- <i>So I don't think I can do it.</i>
- It's a good window. Coop.

842
00:47:10.581 --> 00:47:11.832
<i>I'm sure it is.</i>

843
00:47:13.166 --> 00:47:14.293
Okay.

844
00:47:15.794 --> 00:47:18.964
Well. then how about
you drive and I go in?

845
00:47:19.548 --> 00:47:21.025
That's not how we do it.

846
00:47:21.049 --> 00:47:24.737
Well. maybe we should change how we
do it if your back is gonna be a problem.

847
00:47:24.761 --> 00:47:26.906
It's… it's not a problem.

848
00:47:26.930 --> 00:47:28.056
I just need a little time.

849
00:47:31.476 --> 00:47:32.477
Okay.

850
00:47:33.312 --> 00:47:35.314
- Feel better. <i>viejo</i>.
- Thank you.

851
00:47:37.858 --> 00:47:39.961
Jesus. Sneaking up.

852
00:47:39.985 --> 00:47:41.296
Sorry.

853
00:47:41.320 --> 00:47:42.380
Make some noise. you know.

854
00:47:42.404 --> 00:47:44.489
or I'm gonna have to hang
a bell around your neck.

855
00:47:47.576 --> 00:47:48.720
Is your back bothering you?

856
00:47:48.744 --> 00:47:49.745
Yeah.

857
00:47:53.373 --> 00:47:55.250
Never get old. my friend.

858
00:47:57.669 --> 00:47:58.897
Something on your mind?

859
00:47:58.921 --> 00:48:00.005
Yeah.

860
00:48:01.673 --> 00:48:05.093
I'm wondering how
to write a breakup text.

861
00:48:05.677 --> 00:48:07.221
That's easy. You don't.

862
00:48:08.222 --> 00:48:10.200
Breaking up should
always be done in person.

863
00:48:10.224 --> 00:48:12.202
- Always?
- Yes.

864
00:48:12.226 --> 00:48:13.786
Whether you're dating
or you're breaking up.

865
00:48:13.810 --> 00:48:15.270
the rules are the same.

866
00:48:15.979 --> 00:48:17.564
- What rules?
- Don't be a dick.

867
00:48:18.565 --> 00:48:21.002
It'd be so much easier just to write a text.

868
00:48:21.026 --> 00:48:22.861
Yeah. I'm sure it would.

869
00:48:25.989 --> 00:48:27.199
Something happen?

870
00:48:27.950 --> 00:48:28.951
Yeah.

871
00:48:29.910 --> 00:48:31.161
What's her name?

872
00:48:32.412 --> 00:48:33.455
Delilah.

873
00:48:36.166 --> 00:48:38.102
Ashe's daughter?

874
00:48:38.126 --> 00:48:39.127
Yeah.

875
00:48:40.587 --> 00:48:42.047
Yeah. she's pretty cool.

876
00:48:44.216 --> 00:48:47.445
Well. you gotta deal with Morgan first.

877
00:48:47.469 --> 00:48:48.762
In person.

878
00:48:49.346 --> 00:48:50.698
Okay.

879
00:48:50.722 --> 00:48:52.224
Then see what's up.

880
00:48:53.934 --> 00:48:55.143
All right. well. good talk.

881
00:48:56.186 --> 00:48:57.187
You want a beer?

882
00:48:58.480 --> 00:48:59.481
- Yeah.
- No.

883
00:49:00.315 --> 00:49:02.752
Nice try. But you can get me one.

884
00:49:02.776 --> 00:49:03.986
Okay.

885
00:49:05.529 --> 00:49:06.655
Thank you.

886
00:49:58.957 --> 00:50:01.376
We're looking for a
different fee structure. okay?

887
00:50:02.002 --> 00:50:05.162
Listen. I sat on your side of the table
long enough to know when it's bullshit.

888
00:50:11.303 --> 00:50:14.640
<i>Nothing beats the thrill of hitting
the street with a big chunk of change.</i>

889
00:50:16.433 --> 00:50:18.912
<i>Even when the change
in question isn't yours…</i>

890
00:50:18.936 --> 00:50:19.996
Hey. Coop. How are you?

891
00:50:20.020 --> 00:50:22.147
<i>…and you're hitting
the street under duress.</i>

892
00:50:23.315 --> 00:50:25.108
<i>I was the toast of the town.</i>

893
00:50:27.110 --> 00:50:28.796
<i>Everyone singing for their supper</i>

894
00:50:28.820 --> 00:50:30.072
<i>while they paid for mine.</i>

895
00:50:31.490 --> 00:50:33.760
Don't waste your time chasing medallion.

896
00:50:33.784 --> 00:50:35.827
Roanoke outpaced
them two years straight.

897
00:50:36.495 --> 00:50:38.330
And here I thought
roanoke was a closed fund.

898
00:50:38.872 --> 00:50:40.266
For some people.

899
00:50:40.290 --> 00:50:43.544
<i>It was surreal. really. how
fast I could slip back into it.</i>

900
00:50:44.545 --> 00:50:46.797
<i>The patter. the ball-busting. the bullshit.</i>

901
00:50:48.549 --> 00:50:51.611
<i>And I'd be lying if I said there
wasn't a part of me that had missed it.</i>

902
00:50:51.635 --> 00:50:54.763
<i>Because this… I knew how to do this.</i>

903
00:50:55.389 --> 00:50:56.449
Bullshit.

904
00:50:56.473 --> 00:51:00.078
We can… we wanna be in the
Andrew Cooper business long-term.

905
00:51:00.102 --> 00:51:01.454
But what about the fee structure?

906
00:51:01.478 --> 00:51:03.873
We can talk about a
cap for the first two years.

907
00:51:03.897 --> 00:51:06.209
Well. it was great catching up. Coop.

908
00:51:06.233 --> 00:51:07.752
I knew you'd be back.

909
00:51:07.776 --> 00:51:09.295
It was just a question of when.

910
00:51:09.319 --> 00:51:10.463
I don't believe you.

911
00:51:10.487 --> 00:51:12.173
<i>The game hadn't changed.</i>

912
00:51:12.197 --> 00:51:13.198
<i>It never does.</i>

913
00:51:13.991 --> 00:51:17.160
<i>And I had to remind myself that I
was here to play a different one.</i>

914
00:51:18.120 --> 00:51:20.247
<i>And that game was just getting started.</i>

914
00:51:21.305 --> 00:52:21.407
